    <fr:title text="Direct sum">Direct sum</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>5</fr:month>
      <fr:day>26</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors>
      <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>The direct sum of two vector subspaces <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> of a vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[W]]></fr:tex>, denoted <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \oplus  V]]></fr:tex>, is the set of all vectors that can be uniquely expressed as the sum of a vector from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U]]></fr:tex> and a vector from <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>Formally, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \oplus  V = \{u + v : u \in  U, v \in  V\}]]></fr:tex> where the representation <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w = u + v]]></fr:tex> is unique for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[w \in  U \oplus  V]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>For the direct sum to exist, the subspaces must satisfy the condition <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U \cap  V = \{0\}]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{0\}]]></fr:tex> is the zero vector. This ensures the uniqueness of the representation.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>In the context of a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000U.xml" addr="FA-000U" title="Hilbert Space">Hilbert space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex>, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex> is a closed subspace, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[H = M \oplus  M^\perp ]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M^\perp ]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000V.xml" addr="FA-000V" title="Orthogonal complement">orthogonal complement</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[M]]></fr:tex>. This means every vector <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  H]]></fr:tex> can be uniquely written as <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x = m + n]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[m \in  M]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n \in  M^\perp ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
